Question leetcode -> 50. Pow(x, n)

The Important concepte behind this questions is, if we have n value in negatice form and if we try 
to convert it in positive then it give overflow error or overflow accure, to avoid this problem we 
use Long instead of Int.

â†’ Three important things behind this questions :-
1. Binary Exponutiation
2. 32-bit Integer fect
3. Int VS Long
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

class Solution {
public:
    double solve(double x, long n){
        if(n == 0)
            return 1;

        if(n<0){
            return solve(1/x, -n); 
        }

        if(n % 2 == 0){
            return solve(x*x, n/2);
        }

        if(n % 2 != 0){
        return x * solve(x*x, (n-1)/2);
        }

    return 0;
    }

    double myPow(double x, int n) {
        return solve(x, (long)n);
    }
};
